prime_award_base_transaction_description: PSS - LAW ENFORCEMENT SERVICES AND INFORMATION SHARING - JUSTICE BIOMETRIC IDENTITY SERVICE (JBIS) MODERNIZATION AND O&M
subaward_description:
SUBCONTRACTOR SHALL PROVIDE SUPPORT ACROSS THE JABS/CAS TASK AREAS 3, THE JBIS TASK AREAS 4 AND 9, AND JBIS TASK
AREA 10, BY PROVIDING THE FOLLOWING LCATS:
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· NETWORK ADMINISTRATOR EXPERT
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· HELP DESK/TICKET MANAGEMENT SENIOR
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· BACKEND ENGINEER EXPERT
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PROJECT COORDINATOR EXPERT
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· DATABASE ADMINISTRATOR SENIOR

SCOPE OF SERVICES INCLUDES: 
TRANSITION O&M FROM LEGACY CONTRACTOR
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· CREATE A JABS/CAS O&M TRANSITION PLAN THAT INCLUDES THE TRANSITION WBS/SCHEDULE, ROLES,
STAFFING, GOVERNMENT AND CONTRACTOR TRANSITION RESPONSIBILITIES, AND CRITICAL TRANSITION ISSUES.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· TRANSITION OPERATIONS, MAINTENANCE, AND SUPPORT FROM THE INCUMBENT CONTRACTOR TO A STAFF THAT IS
CAPABLE OF SUPPORTING THE JABS/CAS LEGACY SYSTEM UPON AWARD OF THE CONTRACT.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PARTICIPATE IN TRANSITION ACTIVITIES, AFTER WHICH THE CONTRACTOR SHALL ISSUE A TRANSITION MEMO TO THE
COR TO INDICATE THAT TRANSITION HAS OCCURRED. THE HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE THAT JABS/CAS LEGACY
SYSTEMS CURRENTLY RUN ON WILL REMAIN IN PLACE AND OPERATIONAL DURING THIS TRANSITION. THE
TRANSITION PLAN MUST GUARANTEE UNINTERRUPTED JABS/CAS SERVICE WITH MINIMAL RISK.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PROVIDE THE GOVERNMENT FULLY DOCUMENTED JABS/CAS STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES BASED ON
THE JABS/CAS ATTACHMENTS AS WELL INFORMATION GATHERED DURING THE FIRST 30 DAYS OF THE TRANSITION
PERIOD.
PERFORM O&M OF LEGACY SYSTEMS
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· OPERATE AND MAINTAIN THE JABS/CAS LEGACY SYSTEMS TO INCLUDE ALL ENGINEERING, SUPPORT SERVICES,
HARDWARE, AND SOFTWARE UNTIL THE LEGACY SYSTEM IS DECOMMISSIONED, AFTER ALL USERS AND EXTERNAL
SYSTEM-TO-SYSTEM INTERFACES HAVE TRANSITIONED TO JBIS IN FULL PRODUCTION.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· ENSURE THE SYSTEMS MEET ALL JABS/CAS SLA SERVICE LEVELS AND ALL STANDARD OPERATING PROCEDURES
ARE FOLLOWED AS DEFINED IN THE FORTHCOMING COR APPROVED JABS/CAS STANDARD OPERATING
PROCEDURES.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PERFORM ALL NECESSARY SECURITY PROCESSES FOR THE JABS/CAS LEGACY SYSTEMS.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PERFORM ALL NECESSARY PATCHING AND REMEDIATION OF SECURITY AND MAINTENANCE ISSUES TO ADHERE TO
JABS/CAS SLA SERVICE LEVELS AND APPLICABLE SECURITY POLICY.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· CONTINUE TO PROVIDE ALL REPORTS AND METRICS TO THE GOVERNMENT THAT ARE PART OF THE EXISTING LEGACY
O&M PROCESS.

JBIS DATA MIGRATION SUPPORT
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· SUPPORT CAPTURE ALL BIOMETRIC DATA AS WELL AS METADATA, INCLUDING EBTS, AND CUSTOM DOJ (E.G.,
DOJ CUSTOM TYPE 2 FIELDS DEFINED IN THE JFILE STANDARD) DATA STORED IN THE LEGACY JABS/CAS
SYSTEMS.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· SUPPORT DOCUMENTATION OF HOW DATA WILL BE MIGRATED FROM LEGACY SYSTEMS TO THE JBIS
ENVIRONMENT INCLUDING. A DATA MAPPING SHALL INCLUDE THE SOURCE AND FORMAT OF THE DATA AND
CONVERSION MECHANISM REQUIRED.
FACILITATE TRANSITION TO JBIS
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· SUPPLY ASSISTANCE AND TECHNICAL INFORMATION ABOUT THE LEGACY SYSTEMS TO THE CONTRACTORÃ¢Â‚¬Â„¢S JBIS
TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION TEAM TO FACILITATE TRANSITION AND UNDERSTANDING OF TECHNICAL OPERATIONS.
THIS INCLUDES SUPPLYING AND FACILITATING UNDERSTANDING OF ANY REQUIRED TECHNICAL ARTIFACTS
PERTAINING TO THE JABS/CAS LEGACY SYSTEMS.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PERFORM USER COMMUNITY OUTREACH ASSISTANCE AS PART OF THE TRANSITION TO JBIS. THIS INCLUDES
SUPPLYING THE JBIS TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION TEAM WITH UP-TO-DATE CUSTOMER AGENCY CONTACT
INFORMATION, USER LISTS, AND ANY OTHER OUTREACH ASSISTANCE AND ARTIFACTS THAT MAY BE NECESSARY TO
ENSURE A SMOOTH TRANSITION FROM THE LEGACY JABS/CAS SYSTEM TO THE NEW JBIS SERVICE, WITH THE
PARTICIPATION OF AND APPROVAL OF THE DOJ.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PERFORM TESTING SUPPORT AS NECESSARY TO ENSURE THE TRANSITIONAL STATE OF THE LEGACY JABS/CAS
SYSTEMS IS OPERATING PROPERLY.
DECOMMISSION THE LEGACY JABS/CAS SYSTEMS
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· PLAN AND EXECUTE THE DECOMMISSIONING OF THE JABS/CAS SYSTEMS FROM ALL JABS/CAS
ENVIRONMENTS (TEST/DEV/PROD, ETC.) ONCE THE TRANSITION TO JBIS IS COMPLETE AND THE JABS/CAS
SYSTEMS ARE NO LONGER IN USE.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· SUPPORT ALL EXISTING FRONT-END HARDWARE AND PERIPHERALS USED BY THE LEGACY JABS/CAS SYSTEM,
DECOMMISSIONING OF PERIPHERAL AND LOCAL WORKSTATIONS AT FACILITIES OUTSIDE OF THE JABS/CAS
ENVIRONMENTS WILL NOT BE NECESSARY.
Ã¯Â€ŠÂ· DECOMMISSION THE LEGACY JABS/CAS.... (AND MORE...)
